  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the career options after 12 in PCB?",
  "response": "After completing 12th grade with a focus on Physics, Chemistry, and Biology (PCB), you have a variety of career options in the health and life sciences fields. Here are some popular choices:\n\n1. **Medicine and Surgery**:\n   - **MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery)**: To become a doctor.\n   - **BDS (Bachelor of Dental Surgery)**: To become a dentist.\n   - **BAMS (Bachelor of Ayurvedic Medicine and Surgery)**: Focuses on Ayurveda.\n   - **BHMS (Bachelor of Homeopathic Medicine and Surgery)**: Focuses on homeopathy.\n   - **BUMS (Bachelor of Unani Medicine and Surgery)**: Focuses on Unani medicine.\n   - **BPT (Bachelor of Physiotherapy)**: To become a physiotherapist.\n\n2. **Pharmacy**:\n   - **B.Pharm (Bachelor of Pharmacy)**: To become a pharmacist.\n\n3. **Nursing**:\n   - **B.Sc Nursing**: To pursue a career in nursing.\n\n4. **Biomedical Sciences**:\n   - **B.Sc Biomedical Science**: To work in medical research and diagnostics.\n\n5. **Biotechnology**:\n   - **B.Sc Biotechnology**: Focuses on biotechnological applications in medicine and agriculture.\n\n6. **Genetics**:\n   - **B.Sc Genetics**: Focuses on genetic research and diagnostics.\n\n7. **Microbiology**:\n   - **B.Sc Microbiology**: Focuses on microbial studies and applications.\n\n8. **Biochemistry**:\n   - **B.Sc Biochemistry**: Focuses on chemical processes within and related to living organisms.\n\n9. **Environmental Science**:\n   - **B.Sc Environmental Science**: Focuses on environmental research and conservation.\n\n10. **Forensic Science**:\n    - **B.Sc Forensic Science**: Focuses on crime scene investigation and analysis.\n\n11. **Agriculture**:\n    - **B.Sc Agriculture**: Focuses on agricultural practices, technology, and management.\n\n12. **Food Technology**:\n    - **B.Sc Food Technology**: Focuses on food production, processing, and safety.\n\n13. **Allied Health Sciences**:\n    - **B.Sc Medical Lab Technology**: Work as a medical laboratory technician.\n    - **B.Sc Medical Imaging Technology**: Work as a radiographer.\n\n14. **Nutrition and Dietetics**:\n    - **B.Sc Nutrition and Dietetics**: Focuses on nutritional science and diet planning.\n\n15. **Occupational Therapy**:\n    - **BOT (Bachelor of Occupational Therapy)**: Focuses on helping patients regain lost functionality.\n\n16. **Public Health**:\n    - **B.Sc Public Health**: Focuses on community health and disease prevention.\n\n17. **Research and Academia**:\n    - Pursue a B.Sc in any core biological science followed by postgraduate studies (M.Sc, Ph.D.).\n\n18. **Veterinary Science**:\n    - **BVSc (Bachelor of Veterinary Science)**: To become a veterinarian.\n\nThese are just some of the many options available. You can choose a career path based on your interests, strengths, and career goals. Additionally, entrance exams and eligibility criteria for these courses may vary, so be sure to research them thoroughly.",
